column2: Sunny- calm surface.  First 3 tries disc disappeared in weeds.
Weedy- but weeds seem to settle.
Lots of snails.  Sunny- small waves - recent wind breaks up weeds.  Weeds close to shore!
Sunny- some waves.  Weeds only along shoreline.
Sunny / lots of floating- tangling weeds.  Had to dig out paddleboat from dock.
Very weedy / small particles floating in the water.
Dug paddleboat out of weeds / only 2 fishermen in last week.
Murky.  The lake is the highest I've seen it except immediately after spring thaw.

This is the lowest the lake has been since we owned the property- about 15 years. Our neighbor claims it is the lowest he's seen it in 25 years. The weeds are growing in ever increasing areas of the lake- but we did not have as much difficulty with floating/drifting masses interfering with our dock area.

The lake is at the lowest level in the neighbor's 25 years on the lake.  The weeds were somewhat better this year.  While the weeds reamain spread throughout the lake- they reached close to the surface- but didn't break off in huge floating rafts.  Some fisherman reported difficulty boating- but not as many complaints as the past two years.  In addition- we were able to use our swimming all summer with a minimum of effort compared to the past 3-4 years.  The low lake level permitted us to pick up huge amounts of broken glass and crockery.  Some of this debris was noticeably old- and we wondered if it came from the CCC Camp which was located here.
Lake level extremely low.  Weeds thick near surface- but not drifting in rafts all over lake surface.
Extremely low lake level.  Some weeds floating in rafts around the lake- not as bad as previous years. Fisherman leave right away.
2 loon babies observed on June 16th- but no loon babies on either June 20 or 21st
Heavy rain the past few days.  Lots of particulate in water

MANY floating rafts of weeds impairing swimming and somewhat boating.  Fisherman mentioned he had never seen it so bad. MANY WEEDS MANY WEEDS floating in rafts around lake Many weeds floating in rafts.  Fisherman mentioned it was worst he had seen.
small rafts of weeds floating around
Weeds and still have particles floating in water.  Most of the summer it looks like pollen in water.
Most weeds gone now or piled up and rotting on shore so do not interfere with lake usage.  Sunny- calm
Particles that look like pollen floating in water
somewhat overcast- calm   Clumps of floating slime
patches of floating weed rafts.  Calm.  VERY hot week.
Particles suspended in water.  Large rafts of floating weeds.  Somewhat overcast.
More weeds but wate a bit clearer.  Sunny with light breeze
Same amount of weeds as last week.
Rafts of weeds clustered along shoreline- not floating out in lake.
Rust colored pollen around shoreline and floating in loops out in lake
Rust colored pollen edging lake again after being gone for about a week.  Particles suspended in water out in lake.
2 loons and 2 very aggressive eagles.  One loon on nest- one in nearby water.  Eagles taking turns diving at loons.  Other eagle sitting high in tree close to nest.
Lake was calm and glasslike- sky was partly cloudy.  Reading taken after 3 days of rain.
